Frequently Asked Questions 

What is HOAST

HOAST is a web application providing assistance to create a more open information between the homeowners and the homeowner.

How do I use HOAST

Simply create an account our website then create an HOA group if you are a member of the HOA board member or send a request to join an HOA group if you are a homeowner. Once your request have been approved by a HOA board member, your account will be accepted as one of their homeowners and now have access to the rest of the functions. 

How to Request to join an HOA Group?

Once created a request to join a HOA Group, the HOA member will cross examine your account info and your real life info, to confirm that you are a real member of their HOA. Once confirmed, a group admin will accept your request and add you to the group. 

How do you Register a vehicle to the system?

Hoast provide a way for users to register their own car. Simply go to the dashboard and click Add Vehicle(s) and it will bring you to the Vehicle Registration System. Once Registered the system will create a QR pass for the Vehicle.

Is the QR pass Secure?

The QR codes are created in an encrypted format. The QR code pass system permits admission by validating the person and environment that generated the QR code.